        <div n="160-03P5" type="poem"><head type="note" n="1" xml:id="spp-160-03P5-headnote-1"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-160-03P5-headnote-1-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-160-03P5-headnote-1-line-group-1-line-1"/></lg></head><head type="note" n="2" xml:id="spp-160-03P5-headnote-2"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-160-03P5-headnote-2-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-160-03P5-headnote-2-line-group-1-line-1"/></lg></head><head type="note" n="3" xml:id="spp-160-03P5-headnote-3"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-160-03P5-headnote-3-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-160-03P5-headnote-3-line-group-1-line-1"/></lg></head>
      <lg n="1" type="stanza"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-160-03P5-line-1"><hi rend="display-initial">A</hi><hi rend="underline">TLAS</hi>, we read in ancient Song,</l><l n="2" xml:id="spp-160-03P5-line-2"> Was so exceeding tall and strong,</l><l n="3" xml:id="spp-160-03P5-line-3"> He bore the Skies upon his Back,</l><l n="4" xml:id="spp-160-03P5-line-4"> Just as a Pedlar does his Pack;</l><l n="5" xml:id="spp-160-03P5-line-5"> But, as a Pedlar overpress'd,</l><l n="6" xml:id="spp-160-03P5-line-6"> Unloads upon theÂ·a Stall to rest;</l><l n="7" xml:id="spp-160-03P5-line-7"> Or, when he can no longer stand,</l><l n="8" xml:id="spp-160-03P5-line-8"> Desires a Friend to lend a Hand;</l><l n="9" xml:id="spp-160-03P5-line-9"> So <hi rend="underline">Atlas</hi>, lest the pond'rous Spheres</l><l n="10" xml:id="spp-160-03P5-line-10"> Should sink, and fall about his Ears,</l><l n="11" xml:id="spp-160-03P5-line-11"> Got <hi rend="underline">Hercules</hi> to bear the Pile,</l><l n="12" xml:id="spp-160-03P5-line-12"> That he might sit and rest a while.Y<hi rend="SMALL-CAPS">ET</hi><hi rend="underline">Hercules</hi> was not so strong,</l><l n="13" xml:id="spp-160-03P5-line-13"> Nor could have born it half so long.G<hi rend="SMALL-CAPS">REAT</hi> Statesmen are in this Condition,</l><l n="14" xml:id="spp-160-03P5-line-14"> And <hi rend="underline">Atlas</hi> is a Politician,</l><l n="15" xml:id="spp-160-03P5-line-15"> A <hi rend="underline">premier</hi> Minister of State;<hi rend="underline">Alcides</hi> one of second Rate.</l><l n="16" xml:id="spp-160-03P5-line-16"> Suppose then <hi rend="underline">Atlas</hi> ne'er so wise,</l><l n="17" xml:id="spp-160-03P5-line-17"> Yet when the Weight of Kingdoms lies</l><l n="18" xml:id="spp-160-03P5-line-18"> Too long, upon his single Shoulders,</l><l n="19" xml:id="spp-160-03P5-line-19"> Sink down he must, or find <hi rend="underline">Upholders</hi>.160-03P5   </l></lg></div>
